<!--
    PUF Invoice Example: UC12 - Intermediation Service Invoice (Brokerage Fees)
    
    Use Case: Transparent Intermediary Managing Invoices on Behalf of BUYER (Principal)
    Invoice Type: INTERMEDIATION SERVICE INVOICE (2 of 2)
    Country: France (EXTENDED-CTC-FR profile)
    Format: PUF (Pagero Universal Format) 2.0
    Document Type: Standard Commercial Invoice (Type 380)
    Business Process: B1 (Standard invoice)
    
    Scenario Description:
    Industrial broker (Courtage Industriel Pro SARL - transparent intermediary) issues
    invoice to BUYER (Manufacturing Pharmaceutique Lyon SAS) for intermediation/brokerage
    services. This is the SECOND invoice in the two-invoice model required for transparent
    intermediaries under French VAT law.
    
    VAT Legal Framework:
    - Transparent intermediary services = independent service (BOI-TVA-CHAMP-10-10-40-40, §40)
    - "Les opérations d'entremise pour ce type d'intermédiaire sont considérées comme des
      prestations de service indépendantes de la prestation objet de l'entremise elle-même"
    - Intermediation service follows its own VAT regime (separate from main purchase)
    
    Two-Invoice Model Required:
    - Companion Invoice (Invoice 1/2): Main commercial invoice SELLER → BUYER
      (See PUF_France_UC12_MainInvoice_TransparentIntermediary.xml)
    - THIS INVOICE (Invoice 2/2): Intermediation service invoice Intermediary → BUYER
    
    Services Provided by Transparent Intermediary:
    1. Supplier identification and qualification (market research, due diligence)
    2. Contract negotiation on behalf of BUYER (pricing, terms, delivery conditions)
    3. Purchase order management (placing orders, tracking, expediting)
    4. Invoice processing and validation (receipt, verification, approval workflow)
    5. Supplier relationship management (communications, issue resolution)
    6. Regulatory compliance support (ADR hazmat transport, documentation)
    
    Intermediation Fee Structure:
    - Monthly retainer: 800.00 EUR (management and overhead)
    - Transaction fee: 2% of purchase value (9,050.00 EUR × 2% = 181.00 EUR)
    - Compliance services: 150.00 EUR (hazmat documentation and ADR compliance)
    - Total intermediation fees: 1,131.00 EUR net
    - VAT (20%): 226.20 EUR
    - Total with VAT: 1,357.20 EUR
    
    Key Characteristics (Intermediation Service Invoice):
    - Invoice type 380: Standard commercial invoice for services
    - Business process B1: Standard invoice
    - BG-4 SELLER: Transparent intermediary (Courtage Industriel Pro SARL)
    - BG-7 BUYER: Principal/customer (Manufacturing Pharmaceutique Lyon SAS)
    - BT-49: BUYER's standard electronic address (not routed to intermediary)
    - Payment to intermediary (standard service invoice)
    - Total: 1,357.20 EUR
    - Reference to main invoice UC12-CTI-2026-0456 in notes
    
    Workflow:
    1. Intermediary negotiates contract with SELLER on behalf of BUYER
    2. SELLER issues main invoice to BUYER (managed by intermediary via PA-TR)
    3. Intermediary processes main invoice on behalf of BUYER
    4. Intermediary issues THIS service invoice to BUYER for intermediation fees
    5. BUYER pays intermediary for brokerage services
    6. BUYER pays SELLER for main purchase (managed by intermediary)
    
    French Text Codes Used:
    - #REG# Registration information
    - #PMT# Payment terms
    - #AAI# Additional invoice information (transparent intermediary service note)
    
    Implementation Notes:
    - This is INDEPENDENT service invoice (not routing via SIREN_SERVICECODE)
    - BT-49 uses BUYER's standard address (intermediary invoicing as supplier)
    - Invoice content describes intermediation services rendered
    - Both invoices (main + intermediation) must use e-invoicing platforms (B2B in France)
    - Intermediation service = taxable service under own VAT regime
    - Transaction reference links to main purchase invoice
    
    Date: 2026-02-02
    Reference: XP Z12-014 Annexe A, Section 3.2.11 - Cas n°12
    Reference: BOI-TVA-CHAMP-10-10-40-40, §20 and §40
-->
